#week-title("Three", "Wine Vinegar: The Intermediate Medium")

=== Core Teaching

The *Golden Chain* identifies Wine Vinegar as a key practical example of an
intermediate medium. It sits between the spirit of wine (volatile) and the
corrosive mineral (fixed).

Wine vinegar serves as a medium for bridging kingdoms: it can be used to extract
minerals using a vegetable-derived acid. This month, begin a trial extraction of
a simple mineral (such as sea salt or plant ash) using your strongest wine
vinegar.

=== Topics This Week

- Wine Vinegar as the alchemical "middle"
- Using vegetable Sulphur (vinegar) as a mineral medium
- Practical trial: intermediate extraction

#inner-work[
  *Bridging the Kingdoms*

  Reflect on the concept of "The Bridge." In alchemical terms, a bridge is a
  substance or quality that shares the nature of both things it connects.

  How do you act as a bridge in your own life? Are you the medium between ideas
  and actions? Record your insights in your journal.
]

